page.title: 01LANDSCAPE
page.content: This area is to the east of the city of Winchester. It is approximately in the centre of the county of Hampshire. The area is entirely rural in character and would be best described as 'undulating'. The highest points above sea level being about 100 metres. The area is to the south of the river Itchen which flows westwards and then south to enter the Solent at Southampton. In some ways the block was difficult to survey as it contains no entire settlement;only small parts thereof.The information offered,however,should still give a general impression of life in this area in the year 1985 A.D.
